<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
    <style>
        
        .btn-container {
            position: absolute;
            top: 20px;
            right: 20px;
        }

            .btn-container a {
                margin-left: 10px;
                text-decoration: none;
                color: #333;
                padding: 10px 20px;
                border: 1px solid #333;
                border-radius: 5px;
                transition: all 0.3s ease;
                font-family: 'Press Start 2P', cursive;
            }

                .btn-container a:hover {
                    background-color: #333;
                    color: #fff;
                }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
            margin: auto;
            padding: 20px;
            
        }
            .container h1
            {
                color: #0C2340;
                font-family: 'Press Start 2P', cursive;
            }
            
        /* New styles added */
        .content {
            background-color: #0C2340;
            color: #FFFFFF;
            font-family: 'Press Start 2P', cursive;
            position: relative;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        .content p {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .footer{
            font-family: 'Press Start 2P', cursive;
        }

    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="btn-container">
                <a class="btn btn-outline-info" asp-area="" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Index">Home</a>
                <a class="btn btn-outline-info" asp-area="" asp-controller="Authentication" asp-action="Login">Log In</a>
                <a class="btn btn-outline-info" asp-area="" asp-controller="Authentication" asp-action="Register">Register</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>About us</h1>

        <!-- Wrap the paragraph with a div and apply the new styles -->
        <div class="content">
            <p>

                Two tech enthusiasts, Tu and Thai, set out to create a student management website but ended up with a quirky game advertising platform due to a design mix-up. Instead of scrapping the idea, they blended student management with retro gaming, resulting in the unique Neogeo System. Users navigate through a classic gaming console interface, completing educational missions for experience points and rewards. Despite initial setbacks like a system glitch, they persevered, fixing bugs and enhancing the platform's appeal. Neogeo System transformed into more than just a management tool, becoming a lively hub for students, showcasing how turning mistakes into opportunities can lead to unexpected success.(J4f)
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>